translation.text: Bankstown Line, Inner West & Leppington Line - Delays

Due to signal equipment repairs at Cabramatta some services to the City are experiencing delays. A frequency of services is being maintained however journey times may be longer. Some stopping patterns and platforms may still change at short notice. Please listen to announcements, check information screens and transport apps before boarding services.

Due to signal equipment repairs at Cabramatta, Cumberland Line services may be cancelled. Customers may need to change trains at Granville or Lidcombe to complete their journey. Please allow additional travel time.

Buses are replacing trains between Thornton and Warabrook in that direction only due to a train communications issue.

Change at Maitland for a bus service to continue your journey. Please allow extra travel time, listen to announcements, check information screens, transport apps and see station staff for service updates.

Station Update - Canley Vale, Blacktown, Cabramatta and more

Due to signal equipment repairs at Cabramatta some Cumberland Line services may be cancelled. Customers may need to change trains at Granville or Lidcombe to complete their journey. Please allow additional travel time.

There are changes happening at Central Station during Sydney Metro construction works. Access to certain areas of the station and platforms may be limited, which means using different stairs, escalators and lifts. 

Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff. 

For detailed information please visit https://transportnsw.info/alerts/details#/6049959
Station Update - Yennora, Guildford, Merrylands and more

Due to signal equipment repairs at Cabramatta, a larger than normal service gap maybe experienced. Please allow additional travel time, listen to announcements and information screens for individual service information.

There are changes at Sydenham station during Sydney Metro construction.

T3 Bankstown Line services to the City are available from platform 3 and to Lidcombe and Liverpool from platform 4.

A new Metro concourse is also being constructed at the Northern end of the station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5.

If you need help, please see staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info

Monday 30 November to Thursday 03 December - nightly from 8pm until 4:30am.

The George St entrance/exit to Wynyard Station, Transit Hall and Hunter Tunnel will be closed during station upgrade works. Access to/from the station is still available via Carrington St, York St & Barangaroo. 

Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff or call 9224 2959.
